<p>Given this html:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;header&gt;Some header&lt;/header&gt; &lt;div&gt;     &lt;div class="right-of-header"&gt;should be to the right of header&lt;/div&gt;     &lt;div&gt;Some mor text is here&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I want the content of the first inner div appear to the right, of the header.</p>  <p>Is this possible, without using javascript to actually move the DOM element?</p>  <p>I just found this question: <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11151089/position-one-element-related-to-another-in-css">position one element related to another in CSS</a> but this won't work for me, since I don't know the size and width of the header element. In other words, the solution should be responsive to different layouts.</p>  <p>There is a <a href="https://jsfiddle.net/ex17ak9x/2/" rel="nofollow">jsfiddle for it here</a></p>